House Concurrent Resolution
6011
AMENDMENT HCR6011A
FOR THE INTRODUCED RESOLUTION
Introduced by: Representative Garcia
1 A CONCURRENT RESOLUTION encouraging the Executive Board of the Legislative
2 Research Council to form an interim legislative committee Neurohealth Safety
3 Committee to study and assess unregulated vapor products the regulatory
4 framework under which tobacco and vapor product retail establishments
5 operate.
6 WHEREAS, the health of a state and its institutions depends on the health of its citizens;
7 and
8 WHEREAS, the health of our future citizenry rests on the health of our youth; and
9 WHEREAS, our youth are increasingly using substances that may be deleterious to their
10 mental and physical health in both the long term and the short term; and
11 WHEREAS, vapor products containing intoxicating substances threaten the future health
12 of our state and are often unregulated and of unknown origin; and
13 WHEREAS, the popular perception that the availability of intoxicating vapor products in
14 smoke shops and other retail establishments is a reliable indicator of the products' safety, is
15 erroneous; and
16 WHEREAS, this erroneous perception may be dispelled only by knowledge, information,
17 and insight gained through a careful assessment of the situation in our state;
18 WHEREAS, rules that are unclear in their intent and direction create compliance challenges
19 for tobacco and vapor product retailers; and
20 WHEREAS, the lack of clarity has the potential to affect a variety of regulatory areas,
21 including the payment of fees and the scheduling and conduct of compliance inspections; and
Underscores indicate new language.
Overstrikes indicate deleted language.

HCR6011A 2 HCR6011
1 WHEREAS, a committee that brings interested parties into a conversation about rules and
2 compliance stands the best chance of clarifying the future obligations of all parties;
3 NOW, THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED, by the House of Representatives of the One Hundred
4 First Legislature of the State of South Dakota, the Senate concurring therein, that the
5 Executive Board of the Legislative Research Council be encouraged to form the interim
6 Neurohealth Safety Committee an interim legislative committee to study this important public
7 health issue for the purpose of studying the regulatory framework under which tobacco and
8 vapor product retailers operate and to assess the extent of the need for further regulatory
9 action.
Underscores indicate new language.
